KABUL, Nov. 12 (Xinhua) -- At least 10 people were injured as a blast ripped through a mosque in the Spin Ghar area of the eastern Nangarhar province on Friday, a local official said. The blast, according to the official who declined to be named, took place inside a mosque in Tarili village in Spin Ghar district at 01:30 p.m. local time when the mosque was full of worshippers. Earlier, another official said on the condition of anonymity that the blast occurred inside a mosque in Spin Ghar's neighboring Achin district. An eyewitness has said three worshippers were killed and 15 others injured in the explosion in the mosque. However, local residents said they believed the number of casualties could be higher. This is the second blast inside a mosque in the eastern Nangarhar province over the past one month. The Islamic State (IS) group outfit had claimed responsibility for the previous blast. Enditem